cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about unsupervised sentence representation learning, which is a topic in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The paper also discusses the use of encoder-decoder models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, and therefore could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image captioning datasets, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization ability and transferability of the learned representations, which could relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
